column6: I am a huge fan of the Wunder Under Hi-Rise pants in general. Finally purchased another pair, after wearing my previous pair for the past 5 years and still going strong with those. They're the only pants that seem to never stretch out (or shrink) as long as you follow the proper care instructions. I particularly love the 7/8 length, which for me hits me right at the ankle (I'm 5'5" and would say I have pretty standard/regular inseam). These are so versatile, can be worn for literally anything: yoga, strength training, walks, casual everyday pants, even can be a black tight under a dress in cooler winter months.

column1: Wunder Under High-Rise Tight Full-On Luon 28"
column5: I am smitten with these pants
column6: Many athletic leggings have waistbands with inflexible stitching that pops on your first time pulling them up, these pants don't have that problem. The stitching is very flexible. There is no stitching at the very top of these pants, witch eliminates the seam popping pull-on issue in other leggings brands I've purchased. I wear these doing the stair-stepper and the treadmill as well as training, etc. These leggings are squat-proof and stayed up and in place throughout my entire workout! I've already purchased a second pair in black. I'm 5'3" 127 lbs and fit well in the size 4. These pants are more comfortable than not wearing pants. They feel like a mother's love. One thing to be aware of is that these pants do not wick away excessive sweat (so you've gotta be cool with rocking some sweat badges if you're planning on an intense exertion).

column1: Wunder Under High-Rise Tight Full-On Luon 28"
column6: After hearing so much about Lululemon pants I was interested in trying a pair. My niece said the Wunder Under was the pair to get. At the store I had two to choose from for the black, one with some shine and this pair, which was more of a flat black. My primary intention was to wear these leggings with outfits (not the gym), so I got the flat black. I was told to get a 2 or 4, I opted for the 4. I'm 5'7" 124lbs. and the 4 fit well. I haven't noticed what other reviews have stated, any bagging after wear or pilling. They seem to be holding up really well. I'm pleased so far with the pants and am looking to get another soon.

I bought 2 other Wunder Under leggings a little while ago and they are still like brand new. Fit me amazingly. They have not lost shape and I always wash them on a delicate cycle + line dry to prevent the fabric from getting ruined.
This pair, on the other hand, feels as if it's "older" than my other leggings and I've only worn them a few times!! They're getting loose around the crotch, waist, and ankle area as if I need to trade them in for a new pair. Any looser and they're not going to be very flattering to wear... not happy about this.
Also, the color is not as dark and rich as seen in the photo. They look like almost a whited out faded maroon color. Not really what I was expecting.

column1: Wunder Under High-Rise Tight Full-On Luon 28"
column6:
I purchased these on sale in the ruby wine color in a size 8. I am 5'7" and around 160 lbs, waist is about 29" for reference. As soon as I got them in the mail and put them on, I fell in love! I am going to need more of these in my life, to be quite honest. Rare is the yoga pant that fits so good and is so freakin adorable that I can wear it anywhere I go!
I love the inside pocket to hold my ID and/or credit card and keys if need be. It might even hold my phone as well for runs, but I haven't tried it yet. The color isn't as harsh as I was afraid it might be; I usually shy away from red pants, but I love how neutral and muted these are. They look great with other neutrals -- think white, gray, black, blues of any hue, possibly even that dusty rose color, too.
And now, the bad news and why I gave it one star - I slide when I do arm balances in hot yoga! Granted, I should use my core more in crow pose to keep myself stable (I hear you, yogi veterans, namaste), but it would help if they provided my sweaty arms a little grip to help me get there.
Overall, I do like these leggings a lot. If I could wear them everyday and everywhere I go, I would! Great first pair of Lululemon leggings and will most definitely invest in more.

column6: These are my go-to pants for everything from working out to lounging around to going to class. I think I wear them more often than the average person (1-2 times per week), but they usually last around 6 months for me before the pilling gets noticeable and the fabric loosens. I've been wearing these leggings for at least five years now, I think closer to 6 or 7 even. My first pair of lulu leggings lasted about a full year, if not more (I don't remember exactly), and I wore them with the same frequency/activities. In recent years, I've noticed the quality of these deteriorates much faster. For the third time now I find myself needing to replace them after only 6 months, which is less ideal than I'd expect for $100. I'm not sure if lulu has changed their material/fabric, their manufacturer, or what, but something is definitely noticeably worse about the quality. I still love these leggings (they're fantastic when they're new!), but I do hope Lulu goes back to their former high quality standards, since I'm not sure how many more times I will be willing to pay for leggings with a short lifespan.

My friend with the same pants had the same issue, and someone at the store told her to use a de-fuzzer. I got a de-fuzzer and it got rid of the pilling temporarily, but the pants kept on pilling! I wouldn't expect this much pilling, considering that I've only had the pants for a year (I didn't use these pants for exercise, just casual wear). The pocket is also super odd, because it's located in the middle of the waistband, so it's inconvenient to use. Even though these leggings pill a lot, I do think these leggings are super comfortable though.

column6: I bought my first two pairs of Lulu's about 5 years ago and finally had to retire them at the end of last year because they were so worn out. column6:

I went to the store to purchase another pair yesterday, and could not have been more disappointed. After reading reviews that they were see through, I tested that in the dressing room, and they totally were! Who would pay $100 for SEE THROUGH leggings?!
I am extremely disappointed in Lululemon. They took a quality product (which I loved!!) and completely downgraded the quality. I went to the store ready to purchase them and am so glad I tried them on and listened to the reviews before I bought them again...I would NOT recommend getting these.

column6: I was really excited to buy these because I'd been hearing so many great things about the look, the feel, the quality - people saying they were almost like new even after 7 years and hundreds of washes! I'm a student so as soon as I had money to spare I got these leggings but it was money gone down the drain. After just a few wears the seams started to unravel, the fabric started to pill and became uncomfortable. I was so disappointed - I have bought a lot of lower quality cheaper pants in the past because I knew they wouldn't last too long since my thighs touch and I run a lot, but I expected different from these legendary $100 wunder unders. I was expecting them to last much longer given the reputation of these pants and the price and so called quality promise. First and probably last lululemon purchase for me.
column19: {'LL_response_content': 'I’m so sorry to hear about the unravelling seams and pilling. We stand behind the quality of our gear and would love to make this right. Keep your eye out for an email headed your way.', 'LL_response_date': 'August 3, 2017'}

column1: Wunder Under High-Rise Tight Full-On Luon 28"
column6:
Two weeks ago, I would have told you that these are the greatest yoga pants I've ever owned and that, while they're 100$/pair, they're well worth it. I cannot say that after buying my last pair, and am really disappointed in the decline in Lululemon's quality over the last few years. These pants are see-through even without bending over, and I sized up from my old pair.
I have no idea what Lululemon's quality control procedures are, but these pants are so see-through that I don't think I can ever wear them. All I can say is that I'm short $100 and really disappointed.

column1: Wunder Under High-Rise Tight Full-On Luon 28"
column5: Most comfortable fabirc, but pants don't hold up over time.
column6:
These pants broke my heart. Don't get me wrong - I love them, it's by far the most comfortable pair of pant I've ever owned. The luon fabric is amazing and lives up to "feeling like a second skin".
However, 6 months later (as many of the other reviewers have mentioned - it's like there's a timer on them!), they started pilling, the bottoms stretched out and a hole appeared in the rear. I took the best of care of these pants, too - washed with my one other pair of lululemons, on cold and never put in the dryer. So now they've been retired to house-only pants. I hate to spend $100 on house-only pants.

column1: Wunder Under High-Rise Tight Full-On Luon 28"
column6: I love lululemon. I am not opposed to paying $100 for a quality item that will undoubtedly last for years (as my first 2 WUs have) & give me *at least* $1 per wear or less, basically paying for itself. Except I've found the recent quality of lululemon has plummeted...I do not expect a pair of $100 pants to last less than 6 months! And these are not the only leggings in my rotation, so they have hardly held up to much wear and tear. Wunder Unders have been a tried and true favorite for me because of how flattering they are on...but I invest in my workout clothes for more than that. Not only has the color drastically faded (I follow the washing instructions to a T and lay flat to dry) but the seams have unraveled, pilling, and this week, I discovered a HOLE! I would not recommend spending $100 on these. Incredibly disappointed.

column1: Wunder Under High-Rise Tight Full-On Luon 28"
column6: I purchased these a few days ago without trying on, just grabbed my normal size. Once I got home and put them on, after taking the tags off, I bent over and sure enough they were see through. I have 3 older pairs of these and none of them are that way. I was thinking maybe I got a bad pair or maybe the sizing changed some, since my size hasn't changed, so I brought them to the store and explained what was going on. The workers were very helpful and nice about it, saying that I could grab another pair. I decided to try a size 6 in case the sizing was off, but the 6 was too big and still see through.... I don't know how this continues to be an issue with their leggings. I had to end up getting a pair of align pants since they aren't see through, when what I really wanted was another pair of the wunder unders. I am not happy and very disappointed that I had to settle for a different pair of pants solely because the quality of these pants have not been fixed.

column1: Wunder Under High-Rise Tight Full-On Luon 28"
column5: Feel great but does have flaws
column6: Exactly a week ago today I bought a pair of these during my off period at school.I had to jump through a lot of hoops to be able to get/afford them and the outcome wasn't quite what I was expecting from a $100 pair of leggings. I didn't have time to try them on because I had to walk back to school for another class and I had never bought a pair of leggings from Lulu, even though I have a few pairs of their volleyball shorts. In their shorts I am a size 10, so I went with an 8 for the leggings. I immediately noticed that I kept having to pull them up and that I should've gone with a smaller size, but I didn't take them back and I wore them anyway. After I wore them three times, I noticed that the material was starting to get messed up on the outside of the legs and that the waist was getting even bigger on me. I am on a volleyball team and I play water polo so I am constantly exercising and I need athletic wear. I took the pants back to the store today and I had an excellent experience with customer service and the saleslady was willing to exchange them for a size 6. I am hoping that these will last me long and that they will fit. I tried them on when I got home and my first impression was that I should've gotten a size 4, but I'm hoping that I was wrong and they will fit nicely. Thanks LuluLemon and I can't wait to buy another pair!

column1: Wunder Under High-Rise Tight Full-On Luon 28"
column5: Great feel, stretch out immediately - size down?
column6:
I gave these 2 stars because of the amazing feel this give on my legs - otherwise they deserve a 1.. if that. They're a perfect combination of hugged and still soft and move with my body. Despite that, the waist band stretched out immediately. I wore them with a tunic to work and was truly embarrassed at how often I had to pull these up. For $100 you would think you could manage to create a style that would stay up? I just started shopping with Lululemon, and hope this is not an indication of what's to come. It'd truly be a shame to have such amazing quality with such detrimental issues.
I will be taking these back to see if there's anything that can be done. Obviously I couldn't've known this was going to happen as they fit perfectly when I tried them on, so I'm hopeful they will work with me!
If you do buy - I would suggest sizing down.
